answer: From each shift (dot), you look at the triangle that forms under it. The first left line of the triangle tells you the shift start time and the right line of the triangle stemming from the dot tells you the shift end time. So to determine which shifts start at 12pm, you look at the diagonal lines that slant towards the right from the 12 pm tick mark on the graph, indicating the start time. You can follow the right-slanting diagonal line all the way through to see that shifts M and L start at 12 pm.
